  "description": "Professional QuickBooks and bookkeeping cleanup for U.S. small and mid-sized businesses — reconciled, CPA-ready books rebuilt from a messy or unreconciled state. Fixed-fee, written scope, named Certified ProAdvisor. Typically 2–8 weeks.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Accounting", "href": "/accounting/" },
    { "name": "Bookkeeping", "href": "/accounting/bookkeeping/" },
    { "name": "Cleanup bookkeeping" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "Bookkeeping cleanup",
    "heading": "Messy books are common. They&rsquo;re also fixable.",
    "subheading": "A project-based cleanup that rebuilds accurate, reconciled, CPA-ready books from a messy or unreconciled state &mdash; real reconciliation against actual statements, corrected categorization, resolved discrepancies, documented adjustments. Fixed fee, written scope, named Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor. Typically 2&ndash;8 weeks.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=cleanup", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>A bookkeeping cleanup</strong> is a project-based engagement that reconstructs accurate financial records from a messy or unreconciled state &mdash; real bank reconciliation, categorization corrections, cleared undeposited funds, duplicate/missing-transaction resolution, prior-period error correction, payroll and sales-tax verification, and CPA-ready financial statements. Fixed fee, written scope, typically <strong>2&ndash;8 weeks</strong>.",
    "source": "Distinct from catch-up (behind-but-structured) and monthly (recurring). Not affiliated with Intuit Inc."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Cleanup starts here",
    "heading": "Let&rsquo;s see what your file actually needs.",
    "lede": "Book a free 30-minute diagnostic call. We&rsquo;ll review your QuickBooks file, scope the work honestly, and tell you what cleanup will cost &mdash; in writing &mdash; before any work begins. No pitch, no obligation.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=cleanup", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The engagement</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What a cleanup engagement actually is.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A bookkeeping cleanup is a project-based engagement that reconstructs accurate financial records from a messy or unreconciled state. It covers QuickBooks file cleanup, real bank reconciliation against actual statements, categorization corrections, clearing undeposited funds, fixing duplicate or missing transactions, correcting prior-period errors, verifying payroll and sales-tax entries, and producing CPA-ready financial statements. Most engagements take 2&ndash;8 weeks and are priced as a fixed fee against a written scope.</p>
      <p>Cleanup is distinct from <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/catch-up-bookkeeping/?intent=catch-up">catch-up bookkeeping</a> (which brings behind-but-structured books up to date) and from <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">monthly bookkeeping</a> (which is recurring). Many engagements combine cleanup with catch-up &mdash; clean up the existing periods, catch up the missing months, then transition to monthly.</p>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="pull-quote">
      <p>{{ drift.body | safe }}</p>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Is it time?</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If any of these sound familiar, the answer is yes.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Cleanup, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-deliverables">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The scope</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What cleanup actually delivers.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for d in deliverables %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ d.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The process</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From first call to clean books.</h2>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>{{ s.when | safe }}</strong></p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-compare">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The difference</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What changes when the books are clean.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Cleanup unwinds the accumulated <strong>compounding reconciliation drift</strong> &mdash; here is the before and after, dimension by dimension.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">Bookkeeping before and after a TechBrot cleanup engagement, by dimension.</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Dimension</th>
            <th scope="col">Before cleanup</th>
            <th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">After cleanup</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {%- for row in compare %}
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">{{ row.dim | safe }}</th>
            <td class="vs-table__concede">{{ row.before | safe }}</td>
            <td class="vs-table__us"><strong>{{ row.after | safe }}</strong></td>
          </tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fixed fee, written scope, no hourly billing.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Three tiers; ranges are typical engagements, final pricing follows the diagnostic. See the <a href="/pricing/?intent=pricing">bookkeeping pricing page</a> for ongoing monthly pricing after cleanup.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for t in tiers %}
      <article class="review-card">
        {%- if t.note %}<p class="review-card__role">{{ t.note | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>{{ t.price | safe }}</strong></p>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>For:</strong> {{ t.forWhom | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for b in t.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="/contact/?intent=cleanup">{{ t.cta | safe }} &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who performs the work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A named, credentialed local operator. Not an anonymous offshore team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every TechBrot cleanup is delivered by a vetted local operator &mdash; an independent accounting practice running under TechBrot&rsquo;s brand, standards, and infrastructure. You&rsquo;ll know exactly who is working on your books, how to reach them, and what credentials they hold. Platform-level quality review backs every engagement, and if continuity is ever a question, the platform handles the transition without losing the file context.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-next">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Around the cleanup</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Cleanup is often part of a larger engagement.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in nextSteps %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask before scoping a cleanup.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="cleanup-bookkeeping-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="cleanup-bookkeeping-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
